    </p>
  </div>

  <p class="controls-hint">
    <strong>Link latency</strong> is the simulated network delay — the demo's
    physics. <strong>Animation speed</strong> just scales how fast that plays
    on screen (on-screen time = latency ÷ speed). Slowing the animation only
    stretches the playback; it never changes ordering or which writes collide —
    only latency does that.
  </p>

  <noscript>
